choices.text: the signing of the Vientiane Declaration on ASEAN Community Building in 2004. The Declaration was signed by the ASEAN leaders at the 12th ASEAN Summit in Vientiane, Laos. The Declaration is a milestone in the history of ASEAN as it marks the beginning of the ASEAN Community Building process. The Declaration is a commitment by the ASEAN leaders to build an ASEAN Community by 2015. The ASEAN Community will be a single market and production base, a highly competitive economic region, a region of equitable economic development, and a region fully integrated into the global economy. The ASEAN Community will be a cohesive, peaceful, stable, and resilient community, with a people-oriented, people-centred ASEAN.
